{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "c7e8f901-2345-6789-abcd-ef0123456789",
		"name": "Todo API",
		"description": "REST API for the Spring Boot todo app: JWT auth, workspaces/projects, hierarchical tasks (work-platform–style `/api/tasks` + legacy project-scoped routes), notifications, and related modules.\n\n## Auth\n- `register` (201), `login` (200), `refresh` (200) return `{ \"accessToken\", \"refreshToken\" }`.\n- Protected routes need `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}`.\n- Default token lifetimes: access **15 min**, refresh **14 days** (`application.yml`).\n\n## Suggested flow\n1. **Register** — unique email via `{{$timestamp}}`; tests store tokens and `registeredEmail`.\n2. Or **Login** with `{{registeredEmail}}` + `{{userPassword}}` after you have a user.\n3. **Create project** — saves `projectId`.\n4. Use **Tasks → Work-platform (/api/tasks)** for the same routes/shapes as work-platform (list by `projectId` query, `GET /tree`, members, join-requests, labels, restore, etc.).\n5. Use **Tasks → Project-scoped** for nested create under `/api/projects/{id}/tasks` (parent, labels, assignee, status in one body) and reorder.\n\n## Task response shapes\n- **`/api/tasks/...`** returns work-platform style: `id`, `projectId`, `parentTaskId`, `title`, `status`, `priority`, `dueAt`, `sortOrder`, `path`, `depth`, `members[]`, `createdAt` (no `content`/`labels` in this JSON).\n- **`POST /api/projects/{projectId}/tasks`** still returns the richer legacy task DTO (`content`, `labels`, `assigneeUserId`, `effectiveDueAt`, etc.).\n\n## Errors\n- **400** `{ \"message\": \"...\" }` — validation, bad args, duplicate email.\n- **401** — missing/invalid JWT or bad credentials on login.\n\n## Types\n- Task status: `TODO`, `IN_PROGRESS`, `DONE`.\n- Task priority (string): `LOW`, `MEDIUM`, `HIGH`, `URGENT`.\n- Notification type (read-only in responses): `TASK_DUE_EXPIRED`, `PROJECT_TIMELINE_EXPIRED`.\n- Use ISO-8601 for instants, e.g. `2026-12-31T23:59:59Z`.\n",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
